    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n",
    "import umap.umap_ as umap\n",
    "from scipy.stats import poisson"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def perform_pca(file_path):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    data = np.loadtxt(file_path)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # center the data\n",
    "    mean_vec = np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
    "    centered_data = data - mean_vec\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # computing the covariance matrix\n",
    "    cov_matrix = np.cov(centered_data, rowvar=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # eigendecomposition\n",
    "    eigenvalues, eigenvectors = np.linalg.eigh(cov_matrix)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # sorting eigenvalues and eigenvectors in descending order\n",
    "    sorted_indices = np.argsort(eigenvalues)[::-1]\n",
    "    eigenvalues = eigenvalues[sorted_indices]\n",
    "    eigenvectors = eigenvectors[:, sorted_indices]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # projecting data onto the top 2 eigenvectors\n",
    "    top_eigenvectors = eigenvectors[:, :2]\n",
    "    reduced_data = np.dot(centered_data, top_eigenvectors)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Scatter plot of reduced data\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "    plt.scatter(reduced_data[:, 0], reduced_data[:, 1], alpha=0.5)\n",
    "    plt.title(\"PCA: Data Projected to 2D\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Principal Component 1\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Principal Component 2\")\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "    return reduced_data\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_umap_tsne(file_path):\n",
    "    # Load the data\n",
    "    data = np.loadtxt(file_path)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # UMAP\n",
    "    reducer = umap.UMAP(n_neighbors=15, min_dist=0.1, n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "    umap_embedding = reducer.fit_transform(data)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "    plt.scatter(umap_embedding[:, 0], umap_embedding[:, 1], alpha=0.5, label=\"UMAP\")\n",
    "    plt.title(\"UMAP Visualization\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"UMAP 1\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"UMAP 2\")\n",
    "    plt.grid(True)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # t-SNE\n",
    "    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=30, random_state=42)\n",
    "    tsne_embedding = tsne.fit_transform(data)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "    plt.scatter(tsne_embedding[:, 0], tsne_embedding[:, 1], alpha=0.5, label=\"t-SNE\")\n",
    "    plt.title(\"t-SNE Visualization\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"t-SNE 1\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"t-SNE 2\")\n",
    "    plt.grid(True)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "def poisson_pmf(data, mean):\n",
    "    return poisson.pmf(data, mean) # poisson probability mass function for the given data and mean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def em_algorithm(file_path, max_iter=100, tol=1e-4):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    data = np.loadtxt(file_path)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # sorting the data to separate families with fewer and more children\n",
    "    sorted_data = np.sort(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # splitting the data into two groups\n",
    "    split_index = len(data) // 2  # roughly divide into two halves\n",
    "    group1 = sorted_data[:split_index]  # likely families with family planning\n",
    "    group2 = sorted_data[split_index:]  # likely families without family planning\n",
    "\n",
    "    mean1 = np.mean(group1)  # fewer children (family planning)\n",
    "    mean2 = np.mean(group2)  # more children (no family planning)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # mean1,mean2 = 2, 5\n",
    "    prop1 = 0.5\n",
    "    prop2 = 1 - prop1  # Initial proportions\n",
    "    n = len(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Initial mean1 (with FP): {mean1}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Initial mean2 (without FP): {mean2}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Initial proportions: prop1 = {prop1}, prop2 = {prop2}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for iteration in range(max_iter):\n",
    "        # E-step: calculate responsibilities\n",
    "        resp1 = prop1 * poisson_pmf(data, mean1)\n",
    "        resp2 = prop2 * poisson_pmf(data, mean2)\n",
    "        total_resp = resp1 + resp2\n",
    "        resp1 /= total_resp\n",
    "        resp2 /= total_resp\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # M-step: Update parameters\n",
    "        new_mean1 = np.sum(resp1 * data) / np.sum(resp1)\n",
    "        new_mean2 = np.sum(resp2 * data) / np.sum(resp2)\n",
    "        new_prop1 = np.sum(resp1) / n\n",
    "        new_prop2 = np.sum(resp2) / n\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Check for convergence\n",
    "        if (abs(new_mean1 - mean1) < tol and\n",
    "            abs(new_mean2 - mean2) < tol and\n",
    "            abs(new_prop1 - prop1) < tol and\n",
    "            abs(new_prop2 - prop2) < tol):\n",
    "            break\n",
    "        \n",
    "        mean1, mean2 = new_mean1, new_mean2\n",
    "        prop1, prop2 = new_prop1, new_prop2\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Estimated means: {mean1:.2f} (with FP), {mean2:.2f} (without FP)\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Estimated proportions: {prop1:.2f} (with FP), {prop2:.2f} (without FP)\")\n"
   ]
  },
